Description.
Adult (
Fig. 64
) wingspan 11.0̄12.0 mm. Head with vertex white, frons pale fuscous, face yellowish white. Labial palpus pale yellow, mixed with pale fuscous laterally. Antenna with scape white, tinged with yellow on margins, pecten fuscous; flagellum black dorsally, yellowish white ventrally, dotted with pale yellow on each flagellomere dorsally. Foreleg with femur blackish fuscous on inner surface, tibia black on inner surface, dotted with black near base, at middle, and on distal part laterally, first tarsomere blackish fuscous on inner surface, dotted with black near middle and on distal part laterally, other tarsomeres blackish fuscous distally, remainder yellowish white; midleg mostly yellowish white, femur dotted with black on inner surface at base and middle, tibia dotted with black near base, at middle, and on distal part dorsally, first tarsomere dotted with black at middle and on distal part dorsally, distal parts of second and third tarsomeres black dorsally, distal two tarsomeres black; hindleg white, femur with a gray dot at middle laterally, tibia gray laterally, black distally, each tarsomere black distally. Thorax white; tegula golden fuscous. Forewing ratio 5.5; rust fuscous, with dense transverse fuscous striae; costa with basal 4/5 tinged with yellow, with about 20 transverse blackish-fuscous striae; golden fuscous streak below basal 2/ 5 of fold, with a blackish-fuscous spot distally; fold with a blackish-fuscous spot at distal 1/5, band-shaped, its distal part extending upward to near distal end of upper margin of discal cell, its lower margin sometimes reaching dorsum; distal 3/10 with several white dots along wing margin; dorsal band white, extending beyond tornus, scattered with fuscous scales; blackish-fuscous spot near tornus; cilia golden fuscous on costa and around apex, gray on termen and near tornus. Hindwing and cilia uniformly gray. Abdomen blackish gray dorsally; ventral surface pale yellowish fuscous mixed with gray in male, yellowish white tinged with pale fuscous on third to sixth segments, pale yellowish fuscous on seventh segment in female. Male with lateral lobe of eighth abdominal segment with corner between lines linking apex to dorsal base and to ventral base 72̄73° (n = 8) (
Fig. 300
); female with tergite and sternite straight or nearly so on posterior margin in seventh segment (
Fig. 303
).
